HEADWORD: Synapta
<hw>Syn*ap"ta</hw> <pr>(s⟦icr⟧n*⟦acr⟧p"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>synapto`s</grk> fastened together;
<grk>sy`n</grk> with + <grk>'a`ptein</grk> to fasten.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of slender, transparent holothurians
which have delicate calcareous anchors attached to the dermal plates.
See <xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

